GIT HOOKS & GPG SIGNING SETUP

FOL setup local Git hooks and enable GPG-signed commits.

---

## Make Git hooks executable

chmod +x .githooks/pre-commit

chmod +x .githooks/pre-push

chmod +x .githooks/commit-msg

Tell Git to use the local hooks directory:

git config core.hooksPath .githooks

---

## Enable GPG commit signing

Set your GPG key (replace <key-id> with your actual key ID):

git config --global user.signingkey <key-id>

git config --global commit.gpgsign true

Check your available GPG keys:

gpg --list-secret-keys --keyid-format LONG

Example output:

sec rsa4096/ABCD1234EF567890 2024-05-12 [SC] uid

[ultimate] Isai Gordeev
[isai@example.com](mailto:isai@example.com) sub
rsa4096/XYZ1234567890ABC 2024-05-12 [E]

Use the key after the slash (/) as <key-id> in the command above.

---

